        "text": "I'm having an issue with amarok where it will not show any content in my local collection. I have it set up to scan several folders that contain media. if I tell it to rescan the entire collection I see the progress bar moving for a while, but the local collection in the end remains empty. if I connect my ipod or a usb stick, however, amarok immediately scans it and displays the entire content correctly in my collection.\n\nI have tried starting amarok from the command line and rescanning to see if there are any errors, and do not see anything obvious. this began with an amarok upgrade a while back... I suspect it's related to the switch to an SQL database from sqllite but I am not sure how to troubleshoot this.\n\nany ideas?\n\nLast edited by edward_scott on Wed Dec 15, 2010 5:45 am; edited 1 time in total i looked and found some errors during startup that told me to use mysql_upgrade, and nothing much after. I tried that (mysql_upgrade -u root -p), and restarted mysql. no errors this time. I started up amarok and re-scaned my collection, no change. still no errors in msql:\n\nQuote: jukebox ed # tail /var/log/mysql/mysqld.err\n\n101024 15:48:05 InnoDB: Starting shutdown...\n\n101024 15:48:06 InnoDB: Shutdown completed; log sequence number 0 43665\n\n101024 15:48:06 [Note] /usr/sbin/mysqld: Shutdown complete\n\n101024 15:48:06 [Warning] No argument was provided to --log-bin, and --log-bin-index was not used; so replication may break when this MySQL server acts as a master and has his hostname changed!! Please use '--log-bin=mysqld-bin' to avoid this problem.\n\n101024 15:48:06 InnoDB: Started; log sequence number 0 43665\n\n101024 15:48:06 [Note] Event Scheduler: Loaded 0 events\n\n101024 15:48:06 [Note] /usr/sbin/mysqld: ready for connections.\n\nVersion: '5.1.50-log' socket: '/var/run/mysqld/mysqld.sock' port: 3306 Gentoo Linux mysql-5.1.50-r1\n\nthe other log files in /var/log/mysql are empty."
